(72, 'Art Coming Soon', '', 'Malek Farag', '70c2ceefd07033070eac06aebe9a5e49.jpg', 2, 1, '', '', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">If you are a creative professional looking for some inspiration or love art and design and would like to&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.pixpa.com/blog/web-design-trends\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">keep up with current trends</a>, there are lots of art blogs that might help spark an idea and inspire you.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">We have put together a list of our favorite art blogs that you must follow in the coming year to jumpstart your creativity. This list covers art blogs written by artists, art critics, art lovers, or simply people who appreciate art and like to share their views.</span></p>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574743033-389837-art-blogsjpg.png\" data-image=\"rfxl93y7ms78\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574743033-389837-art-blogsjpg.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 2em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Here is our curated list of the Top 25 Art Blogs and Online Magazines</span></h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://hifructose.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Hi-Fructose</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679607-145564-hi-fructose-magazine-the-new-contemporary-art-magazinepng.png\" data-image=\"6ub7vi0t42tk\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679607-145564-hi-fructose-magazine-the-new-contemporary-art-magazinepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Hi-Fructose was founded by two artists by the name of Attaboy and Annie Owen in the year 2005. It is a magazine that is published quarterly. The art blog part is headed by Andy Smith. Hi-Fructose revolves around contemporary art and showcases the best artists of recent times. There is no fixed genre that it emphasizes. Each post highlights the works of a different artist, focusing on one notable work. A typical Hi-Fructose post also describes how the artist came up with the idea and the process behind the creation of the work. The post contains information about the artist and his/her quotes. Hi-Fructose appreciates and celebrates original artwork and inspires new artists to come up with better works. The blog is full of talented contributors and readers can expect as many as four posts every day!</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.artnews.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ARTnews Magazine&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679621-673801-artnews-com-the-leading-source-for-art-news-art-event-coveragepng.png\" data-image=\"zo9z4s6jzq9w\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679621-673801-artnews-com-the-leading-source-for-art-news-art-event-coveragepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Artnews is the oldest art magazine in the world. It would come as no surprise then that the content is rich and varied. Artnews has an art blog as well which publishes posts about art events, trends, artist profiles, art in general, as well as trending issues. With more than 703,000 followers on Instagram and 227,000 likes on Facebook, Artnews is also one of the most popular art blogs around. The blog has a separate section for reviews as well that contains hard-hitting journalism, a high-quality critique of artworks, and insightful reports. The &lsquo;retrospective&rsquo; section looks back at artworks from the past and treats readers with valuable opinions and meaningful research. The blog has a wide reader base that includes both amateurs as well as experts. With as many as 8 posts every day, ARTnews is a rich database of articles and resources related to art.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.artforum.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Artforum</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679635-45144-artforum-internationalpng.png\" data-image=\"9c9pj4naus8v\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679635-45144-artforum-internationalpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Artforum is a New York-based art blog. It revolves around contemporary art and publishes enlightening critiques of visual art exhibitions. It also publishes news and articles on trending topics and issues. The blog has a separate section for&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.artandeducation.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Art and Education</a>&nbsp;which has resources for aspiring artists who want to follow a career in their passion. Artforum has columns, shows, and a print media section as well. The blog also showcases works of present-day artists and provides valuable reviews. A part of the blog is completely dedicated to this. All in all, this blog brings together all art-related things in one place. You can even purchase merchandise and other artworks via this platform. It is a rather happening place for art enthusiasts with a minimum of 7 posts every day. The blog has 600,000 followers on Instagram and Twitter.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.contemporaryartdaily.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Contemporary Art Daily&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679650-898020-contemporary-art-daily-png.png\" data-image=\"kvtrm4lj9ze7\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679650-898020-contemporary-art-daily-png.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">As the name suggests, this blog publishes content that talks about contemporary art. Started in the month of November in 2008, readers can expect a minimum of 3 posts from them every day. The blog has content that covers contemporary art events and exhibitions organized on a global level. Contemporary Art Daily also showcases submissions by amateur artists. The blog contains archives, information about art exhibitions, reviews, trending matters, and much more. Art enthusiasts can sign up to receive weekly emails from the blog. A&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.pixpa.com/blog/how-to-write-blog-post\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">typical blog post</a>&nbsp;about an artwork displayed in an exhibition contains the name and bio of the artist, the artwork itself, the venue, date, and the organizers of the exhibition. The post sometimes contains a slideshow of all the works of the art exhibition.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.frankie.com.au/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Frankie Magazine</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574741390-876010-frankiejpg.png\" data-image=\"vqg7jh2t3zzr\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574741390-876010-frankiejpg.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\" /><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">This art publication from Australia is one of the most popular art blogs in the country. Content on the Frankie blog covers a wide range of domains. Art, craft, photography, design, music, film, and books are surprisingly just a few of them. You can find articles on cuisine, vintage artworks, and fashion as well. The Frankie blog also has a podcast section where you can enjoy the latest content published by them. Since Frankie Magazine is sort of like a Jack of all trades, its versatility is one of the major attractions for readers and art enthusiasts. The publication started in 2011 and comes up with a new post every week. You can also shop for products like diaries, calendars, books, and of course, printed issues of the Frankie magazine.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://moussemagazine.it/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Mousse&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679687-140082-mousse-magazinepng.png\" data-image=\"240qzk97qq85\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679687-140082-mousse-magazinepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Another art publication that dedicates its content to mostly contemporary artworks, Mousse originated in Milan, Italy in the year 2006. It is published twice a month in English and Italian. Mousse is a classy magazine that publishes interviews with some of the most reputed artists and curators from around the globe. Along with that, Mousse contains essays and critical analysis of contemporary artworks by esteemed critics and artists. It is printed in a pleasant tabloid format. The online blog also contains a rich variety of articles and distinctive editorials. You can also subscribe to emails from Mousse to keep yourself updated about the ongoings in the art world. Mousse is one of the best art blogs and magazines in our opinion. The publication radiates class and finesse.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.cassart.co.uk/blog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cass Art / Art Supplies Blog&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679722-516142-cass-artpng.png\" data-image=\"vfzvjs7ps9sz\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679722-516142-cass-artpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Cass Art is one of the best art blogs in the United Kingdom. Originating from London, Cass Art aims to inspire and propel new artists to the forefront. In general, Cass Art is an art supplies blog that ensures that talented and creative artists get the best prices on the highest quality of art materials in the market. The blog started in the year 2012 and since then has gathered more than 50,000 followers on Twitter and Facebook. The official website has categorized art supplies into painting, drawing, surfaces, craft, etc. It also has a separate section for products that are meant for kids. Not only this, Cass Art posts information about upcoming events in the world of art. Lastly, the blog also has information about art workshops in most of the important cities of England like Manchester, London, Liverpool, and Birmingham.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://blog.lostartpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Lost Art Press</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679743-25840-lost-art-presspng.png\" data-image=\"4bl6ud6qz9ay\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679743-25840-lost-art-presspng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">The Lost Art Press was founded in 2007 by two woodworkers, Jeff Hoffmann and Christopher Schwarz. The blog focuses on woodworking and publications related to it. You can find books, archives, and resources on the Lost Art Press. The aim of the blog is to create awareness about the &lsquo;lost art&rsquo; of woodworking. The blog encourages high-quality books, which are made with the finest of materials. The founding members share half of the profit with the authors and give them due credit. Apart from books, you can also buy tools like hammers, electrical saws, scrapers, and other similar articles. There is also a section for clothing and accessories. The blog has a small following on social media but don\'t let the numbers fool you. The blog is a hotspot for artists and woodworkers. Apart from the online blog, the Lost Art Press also sells books via small to medium-sized retailers.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.thisiscolossal.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Colossal</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679771-425069-colossal-art-design-and-visual-culture-png.png\" data-image=\"mllpqozderyn\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679771-425069-colossal-art-design-and-visual-culture-png.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">If the previous entry on the list wasn&rsquo;t impactful enough, Colossal stands true to its name and is one of&nbsp; the biggest art blogs in the United States. Launched in 2010 in Illinois, the blog publishes content about visual arts. Colossal covers a wide range of topics with the likes of photography, animation, design, painting, and drawing bossing the show. You can also find stuff related to installation art as well as street art. The blog is a vibrant collection of resources related to art, design, and visual culture. Colossal has a whopping fan following of more than a million followers on social media. The range of content is so diverse that it is fascinating. Head on to the blog and click on the &lsquo;More&rsquo; section to see a variety of categories and topics that you can explore. Lastly, you can buy funky merchandise in the e-commerce section of Colossal.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://spoke-art.com/blogs/news\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Spoke Art&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679788-742731-spoke-art-blog-spoke-artpng.png\" data-image=\"j910wgexx5ic\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679788-742731-spoke-art-blog-spoke-artpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Spoke Art is an Art gallery in San Francisco. It also publishes articles, reviews, and news. The blog celebrates pop art and contemporary art and publishes content related to them. Spoke Art also organizes art exhibitions and events. It also publishes artists&rsquo; profiles and editions. On the official website of the Spoke Art, you can check out merchandise like pins, books, clothes, collectibles, and toys. All in all, the Spoke Art space is a vibrant and happening place where art enthusiasts can enjoy original content by some of the most creative artists in the world. Articles and reviews by Spoke Art are insightful, resourceful, and valuable. Once you visit a page on the website which is dedicated to a particular genre of art, you can browse through the related events, featured exhibitions, and featured artists. You can purchase magazines and printed editions of Spoke Art as well.</span></p>', '2021-04-18', ''),
(73, 'Ent Coming Soon', '', 'Malek Farag', '70c2ceefd07033070eac06aebe9a5e49.jpg', 3, 1, '', '', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">If you are a creative professional looking for some inspiration or love art and design and would like to&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.pixpa.com/blog/web-design-trends\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">keep up with current trends</a>, there are lots of art blogs that might help spark an idea and inspire you.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">We have put together a list of our favorite art blogs that you must follow in the coming year to jumpstart your creativity. This list covers art blogs written by artists, art critics, art lovers, or simply people who appreciate art and like to share their views.</span></p>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574743033-389837-art-blogsjpg.png\" data-image=\"rfxl93y7ms78\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574743033-389837-art-blogsjpg.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 2em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Here is our curated list of the Top 25 Art Blogs and Online Magazines</span></h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://hifructose.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Hi-Fructose</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679607-145564-hi-fructose-magazine-the-new-contemporary-art-magazinepng.png\" data-image=\"6ub7vi0t42tk\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679607-145564-hi-fructose-magazine-the-new-contemporary-art-magazinepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Hi-Fructose was founded by two artists by the name of Attaboy and Annie Owen in the year 2005. It is a magazine that is published quarterly. The art blog part is headed by Andy Smith. Hi-Fructose revolves around contemporary art and showcases the best artists of recent times. There is no fixed genre that it emphasizes. Each post highlights the works of a different artist, focusing on one notable work. A typical Hi-Fructose post also describes how the artist came up with the idea and the process behind the creation of the work. The post contains information about the artist and his/her quotes. Hi-Fructose appreciates and celebrates original artwork and inspires new artists to come up with better works. The blog is full of talented contributors and readers can expect as many as four posts every day!</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.artnews.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ARTnews Magazine&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679621-673801-artnews-com-the-leading-source-for-art-news-art-event-coveragepng.png\" data-image=\"zo9z4s6jzq9w\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679621-673801-artnews-com-the-leading-source-for-art-news-art-event-coveragepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Artnews is the oldest art magazine in the world. It would come as no surprise then that the content is rich and varied. Artnews has an art blog as well which publishes posts about art events, trends, artist profiles, art in general, as well as trending issues. With more than 703,000 followers on Instagram and 227,000 likes on Facebook, Artnews is also one of the most popular art blogs around. The blog has a separate section for reviews as well that contains hard-hitting journalism, a high-quality critique of artworks, and insightful reports. The &lsquo;retrospective&rsquo; section looks back at artworks from the past and treats readers with valuable opinions and meaningful research. The blog has a wide reader base that includes both amateurs as well as experts. With as many as 8 posts every day, ARTnews is a rich database of articles and resources related to art.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.artforum.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Artforum</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679635-45144-artforum-internationalpng.png\" data-image=\"9c9pj4naus8v\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679635-45144-artforum-internationalpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Artforum is a New York-based art blog. It revolves around contemporary art and publishes enlightening critiques of visual art exhibitions. It also publishes news and articles on trending topics and issues. The blog has a separate section for&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.artandeducation.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Art and Education</a>&nbsp;which has resources for aspiring artists who want to follow a career in their passion. Artforum has columns, shows, and a print media section as well. The blog also showcases works of present-day artists and provides valuable reviews. A part of the blog is completely dedicated to this. All in all, this blog brings together all art-related things in one place. You can even purchase merchandise and other artworks via this platform. It is a rather happening place for art enthusiasts with a minimum of 7 posts every day. The blog has 600,000 followers on Instagram and Twitter.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.contemporaryartdaily.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Contemporary Art Daily&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679650-898020-contemporary-art-daily-png.png\" data-image=\"kvtrm4lj9ze7\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679650-898020-contemporary-art-daily-png.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">As the name suggests, this blog publishes content that talks about contemporary art. Started in the month of November in 2008, readers can expect a minimum of 3 posts from them every day. The blog has content that covers contemporary art events and exhibitions organized on a global level. Contemporary Art Daily also showcases submissions by amateur artists. The blog contains archives, information about art exhibitions, reviews, trending matters, and much more. Art enthusiasts can sign up to receive weekly emails from the blog. A&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.pixpa.com/blog/how-to-write-blog-post\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">typical blog post</a>&nbsp;about an artwork displayed in an exhibition contains the name and bio of the artist, the artwork itself, the venue, date, and the organizers of the exhibition. The post sometimes contains a slideshow of all the works of the art exhibition.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.frankie.com.au/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Frankie Magazine</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574741390-876010-frankiejpg.png\" data-image=\"vqg7jh2t3zzr\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574741390-876010-frankiejpg.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\" /><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">This art publication from Australia is one of the most popular art blogs in the country. Content on the Frankie blog covers a wide range of domains. Art, craft, photography, design, music, film, and books are surprisingly just a few of them. You can find articles on cuisine, vintage artworks, and fashion as well. The Frankie blog also has a podcast section where you can enjoy the latest content published by them. Since Frankie Magazine is sort of like a Jack of all trades, its versatility is one of the major attractions for readers and art enthusiasts. The publication started in 2011 and comes up with a new post every week. You can also shop for products like diaries, calendars, books, and of course, printed issues of the Frankie magazine.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://moussemagazine.it/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Mousse&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679687-140082-mousse-magazinepng.png\" data-image=\"240qzk97qq85\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679687-140082-mousse-magazinepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Another art publication that dedicates its content to mostly contemporary artworks, Mousse originated in Milan, Italy in the year 2006. It is published twice a month in English and Italian. Mousse is a classy magazine that publishes interviews with some of the most reputed artists and curators from around the globe. Along with that, Mousse contains essays and critical analysis of contemporary artworks by esteemed critics and artists. It is printed in a pleasant tabloid format. The online blog also contains a rich variety of articles and distinctive editorials. You can also subscribe to emails from Mousse to keep yourself updated about the ongoings in the art world. Mousse is one of the best art blogs and magazines in our opinion. The publication radiates class and finesse.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.cassart.co.uk/blog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cass Art / Art Supplies Blog&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679722-516142-cass-artpng.png\" data-image=\"vfzvjs7ps9sz\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679722-516142-cass-artpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Cass Art is one of the best art blogs in the United Kingdom. Originating from London, Cass Art aims to inspire and propel new artists to the forefront. In general, Cass Art is an art supplies blog that ensures that talented and creative artists get the best prices on the highest quality of art materials in the market. The blog started in the year 2012 and since then has gathered more than 50,000 followers on Twitter and Facebook. The official website has categorized art supplies into painting, drawing, surfaces, craft, etc. It also has a separate section for products that are meant for kids. Not only this, Cass Art posts information about upcoming events in the world of art. Lastly, the blog also has information about art workshops in most of the important cities of England like Manchester, London, Liverpool, and Birmingham.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://blog.lostartpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Lost Art Press</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679743-25840-lost-art-presspng.png\" data-image=\"4bl6ud6qz9ay\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679743-25840-lost-art-presspng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">The Lost Art Press was founded in 2007 by two woodworkers, Jeff Hoffmann and Christopher Schwarz. The blog focuses on woodworking and publications related to it. You can find books, archives, and resources on the Lost Art Press. The aim of the blog is to create awareness about the &lsquo;lost art&rsquo; of woodworking. The blog encourages high-quality books, which are made with the finest of materials. The founding members share half of the profit with the authors and give them due credit. Apart from books, you can also buy tools like hammers, electrical saws, scrapers, and other similar articles. There is also a section for clothing and accessories. The blog has a small following on social media but don\'t let the numbers fool you. The blog is a hotspot for artists and woodworkers. Apart from the online blog, the Lost Art Press also sells books via small to medium-sized retailers.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.thisiscolossal.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Colossal</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679771-425069-colossal-art-design-and-visual-culture-png.png\" data-image=\"mllpqozderyn\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679771-425069-colossal-art-design-and-visual-culture-png.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">If the previous entry on the list wasn&rsquo;t impactful enough, Colossal stands true to its name and is one of&nbsp; the biggest art blogs in the United States. Launched in 2010 in Illinois, the blog publishes content about visual arts. Colossal covers a wide range of topics with the likes of photography, animation, design, painting, and drawing bossing the show. You can also find stuff related to installation art as well as street art. The blog is a vibrant collection of resources related to art, design, and visual culture. Colossal has a whopping fan following of more than a million followers on social media. The range of content is so diverse that it is fascinating. Head on to the blog and click on the &lsquo;More&rsquo; section to see a variety of categories and topics that you can explore. Lastly, you can buy funky merchandise in the e-commerce section of Colossal.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://spoke-art.com/blogs/news\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Spoke Art&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679788-742731-spoke-art-blog-spoke-artpng.png\" data-image=\"j910wgexx5ic\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679788-742731-spoke-art-blog-spoke-artpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Spoke Art is an Art gallery in San Francisco. It also publishes articles, reviews, and news. The blog celebrates pop art and contemporary art and publishes content related to them. Spoke Art also organizes art exhibitions and events. It also publishes artists&rsquo; profiles and editions. On the official website of the Spoke Art, you can check out merchandise like pins, books, clothes, collectibles, and toys. All in all, the Spoke Art space is a vibrant and happening place where art enthusiasts can enjoy original content by some of the most creative artists in the world. Articles and reviews by Spoke Art are insightful, resourceful, and valuable. Once you visit a page on the website which is dedicated to a particular genre of art, you can browse through the related events, featured exhibitions, and featured artists. You can purchase magazines and printed editions of Spoke Art as well.</span></p>', '2021-04-18', '');
INSERT INTO `tbl_blog` (`blog_id`, `blog_title`, `blog_subheader`, `blog_author`, `blog_image`, `blog_category`, `blog_published`, `blog_end_link`, `blog_yt_video`, `blog_body`, `blog_date`, `blog_tags`) VALUES
(69, 'Food Coming Soon', '', 'Malek Farag', '70c2ceefd07033070eac06aebe9a5e49.jpg', 4, 1, '', '', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">If you are a creative professional looking for some inspiration or love art and design and would like to&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.pixpa.com/blog/web-design-trends\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">keep up with current trends</a>, there are lots of art blogs that might help spark an idea and inspire you.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">We have put together a list of our favorite art blogs that you must follow in the coming year to jumpstart your creativity. This list covers art blogs written by artists, art critics, art lovers, or simply people who appreciate art and like to share their views.</span></p>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574743033-389837-art-blogsjpg.png\" data-image=\"rfxl93y7ms78\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574743033-389837-art-blogsjpg.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 2em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Here is our curated list of the Top 25 Art Blogs and Online Magazines</span></h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://hifructose.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Hi-Fructose</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679607-145564-hi-fructose-magazine-the-new-contemporary-art-magazinepng.png\" data-image=\"6ub7vi0t42tk\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679607-145564-hi-fructose-magazine-the-new-contemporary-art-magazinepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Hi-Fructose was founded by two artists by the name of Attaboy and Annie Owen in the year 2005. It is a magazine that is published quarterly. The art blog part is headed by Andy Smith. Hi-Fructose revolves around contemporary art and showcases the best artists of recent times. There is no fixed genre that it emphasizes. Each post highlights the works of a different artist, focusing on one notable work. A typical Hi-Fructose post also describes how the artist came up with the idea and the process behind the creation of the work. The post contains information about the artist and his/her quotes. Hi-Fructose appreciates and celebrates original artwork and inspires new artists to come up with better works. The blog is full of talented contributors and readers can expect as many as four posts every day!</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.artnews.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ARTnews Magazine&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679621-673801-artnews-com-the-leading-source-for-art-news-art-event-coveragepng.png\" data-image=\"zo9z4s6jzq9w\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679621-673801-artnews-com-the-leading-source-for-art-news-art-event-coveragepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Artnews is the oldest art magazine in the world. It would come as no surprise then that the content is rich and varied. Artnews has an art blog as well which publishes posts about art events, trends, artist profiles, art in general, as well as trending issues. With more than 703,000 followers on Instagram and 227,000 likes on Facebook, Artnews is also one of the most popular art blogs around. The blog has a separate section for reviews as well that contains hard-hitting journalism, a high-quality critique of artworks, and insightful reports. The &lsquo;retrospective&rsquo; section looks back at artworks from the past and treats readers with valuable opinions and meaningful research. The blog has a wide reader base that includes both amateurs as well as experts. With as many as 8 posts every day, ARTnews is a rich database of articles and resources related to art.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.artforum.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Artforum</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679635-45144-artforum-internationalpng.png\" data-image=\"9c9pj4naus8v\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679635-45144-artforum-internationalpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Artforum is a New York-based art blog. It revolves around contemporary art and publishes enlightening critiques of visual art exhibitions. It also publishes news and articles on trending topics and issues. The blog has a separate section for&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.artandeducation.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Art and Education</a>&nbsp;which has resources for aspiring artists who want to follow a career in their passion. Artforum has columns, shows, and a print media section as well. The blog also showcases works of present-day artists and provides valuable reviews. A part of the blog is completely dedicated to this. All in all, this blog brings together all art-related things in one place. You can even purchase merchandise and other artworks via this platform. It is a rather happening place for art enthusiasts with a minimum of 7 posts every day. The blog has 600,000 followers on Instagram and Twitter.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.contemporaryartdaily.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Contemporary Art Daily&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679650-898020-contemporary-art-daily-png.png\" data-image=\"kvtrm4lj9ze7\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679650-898020-contemporary-art-daily-png.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">As the name suggests, this blog publishes content that talks about contemporary art. Started in the month of November in 2008, readers can expect a minimum of 3 posts from them every day. The blog has content that covers contemporary art events and exhibitions organized on a global level. Contemporary Art Daily also showcases submissions by amateur artists. The blog contains archives, information about art exhibitions, reviews, trending matters, and much more. Art enthusiasts can sign up to receive weekly emails from the blog. A&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.pixpa.com/blog/how-to-write-blog-post\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">typical blog post</a>&nbsp;about an artwork displayed in an exhibition contains the name and bio of the artist, the artwork itself, the venue, date, and the organizers of the exhibition. The post sometimes contains a slideshow of all the works of the art exhibition.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.frankie.com.au/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Frankie Magazine</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574741390-876010-frankiejpg.png\" data-image=\"vqg7jh2t3zzr\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574741390-876010-frankiejpg.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\" /><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">This art publication from Australia is one of the most popular art blogs in the country. Content on the Frankie blog covers a wide range of domains. Art, craft, photography, design, music, film, and books are surprisingly just a few of them. You can find articles on cuisine, vintage artworks, and fashion as well. The Frankie blog also has a podcast section where you can enjoy the latest content published by them. Since Frankie Magazine is sort of like a Jack of all trades, its versatility is one of the major attractions for readers and art enthusiasts. The publication started in 2011 and comes up with a new post every week. You can also shop for products like diaries, calendars, books, and of course, printed issues of the Frankie magazine.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://moussemagazine.it/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Mousse&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679687-140082-mousse-magazinepng.png\" data-image=\"240qzk97qq85\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679687-140082-mousse-magazinepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Another art publication that dedicates its content to mostly contemporary artworks, Mousse originated in Milan, Italy in the year 2006. It is published twice a month in English and Italian. Mousse is a classy magazine that publishes interviews with some of the most reputed artists and curators from around the globe. Along with that, Mousse contains essays and critical analysis of contemporary artworks by esteemed critics and artists. It is printed in a pleasant tabloid format. The online blog also contains a rich variety of articles and distinctive editorials. You can also subscribe to emails from Mousse to keep yourself updated about the ongoings in the art world. Mousse is one of the best art blogs and magazines in our opinion. The publication radiates class and finesse.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.cassart.co.uk/blog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cass Art / Art Supplies Blog&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679722-516142-cass-artpng.png\" data-image=\"vfzvjs7ps9sz\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679722-516142-cass-artpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Cass Art is one of the best art blogs in the United Kingdom. Originating from London, Cass Art aims to inspire and propel new artists to the forefront. In general, Cass Art is an art supplies blog that ensures that talented and creative artists get the best prices on the highest quality of art materials in the market. The blog started in the year 2012 and since then has gathered more than 50,000 followers on Twitter and Facebook. The official website has categorized art supplies into painting, drawing, surfaces, craft, etc. It also has a separate section for products that are meant for kids. Not only this, Cass Art posts information about upcoming events in the world of art. Lastly, the blog also has information about art workshops in most of the important cities of England like Manchester, London, Liverpool, and Birmingham.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://blog.lostartpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Lost Art Press</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679743-25840-lost-art-presspng.png\" data-image=\"4bl6ud6qz9ay\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679743-25840-lost-art-presspng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">The Lost Art Press was founded in 2007 by two woodworkers, Jeff Hoffmann and Christopher Schwarz. The blog focuses on woodworking and publications related to it. You can find books, archives, and resources on the Lost Art Press. The aim of the blog is to create awareness about the &lsquo;lost art&rsquo; of woodworking. The blog encourages high-quality books, which are made with the finest of materials. The founding members share half of the profit with the authors and give them due credit. Apart from books, you can also buy tools like hammers, electrical saws, scrapers, and other similar articles. There is also a section for clothing and accessories. The blog has a small following on social media but don\'t let the numbers fool you. The blog is a hotspot for artists and woodworkers. Apart from the online blog, the Lost Art Press also sells books via small to medium-sized retailers.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.thisiscolossal.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Colossal</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679771-425069-colossal-art-design-and-visual-culture-png.png\" data-image=\"mllpqozderyn\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679771-425069-colossal-art-design-and-visual-culture-png.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">If the previous entry on the list wasn&rsquo;t impactful enough, Colossal stands true to its name and is one of&nbsp; the biggest art blogs in the United States. Launched in 2010 in Illinois, the blog publishes content about visual arts. Colossal covers a wide range of topics with the likes of photography, animation, design, painting, and drawing bossing the show. You can also find stuff related to installation art as well as street art. The blog is a vibrant collection of resources related to art, design, and visual culture. Colossal has a whopping fan following of more than a million followers on social media. The range of content is so diverse that it is fascinating. Head on to the blog and click on the &lsquo;More&rsquo; section to see a variety of categories and topics that you can explore. Lastly, you can buy funky merchandise in the e-commerce section of Colossal.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://spoke-art.com/blogs/news\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Spoke Art&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679788-742731-spoke-art-blog-spoke-artpng.png\" data-image=\"j910wgexx5ic\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679788-742731-spoke-art-blog-spoke-artpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Spoke Art is an Art gallery in San Francisco. It also publishes articles, reviews, and news. The blog celebrates pop art and contemporary art and publishes content related to them. Spoke Art also organizes art exhibitions and events. It also publishes artists&rsquo; profiles and editions. On the official website of the Spoke Art, you can check out merchandise like pins, books, clothes, collectibles, and toys. All in all, the Spoke Art space is a vibrant and happening place where art enthusiasts can enjoy original content by some of the most creative artists in the world. Articles and reviews by Spoke Art are insightful, resourceful, and valuable. Once you visit a page on the website which is dedicated to a particular genre of art, you can browse through the related events, featured exhibitions, and featured artists. You can purchase magazines and printed editions of Spoke Art as well.</span></p>', '2021-04-18', ''),
(70, 'Lifestyle Coming Soon', '', 'Malek Farag', '70c2ceefd07033070eac06aebe9a5e49.jpg', 5, 1, '', '', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">If you are a creative professional looking for some inspiration or love art and design and would like to&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.pixpa.com/blog/web-design-trends\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">keep up with current trends</a>, there are lots of art blogs that might help spark an idea and inspire you.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">We have put together a list of our favorite art blogs that you must follow in the coming year to jumpstart your creativity. This list covers art blogs written by artists, art critics, art lovers, or simply people who appreciate art and like to share their views.</span></p>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574743033-389837-art-blogsjpg.png\" data-image=\"rfxl93y7ms78\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574743033-389837-art-blogsjpg.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 2em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Here is our curated list of the Top 25 Art Blogs and Online Magazines</span></h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://hifructose.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Hi-Fructose</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679607-145564-hi-fructose-magazine-the-new-contemporary-art-magazinepng.png\" data-image=\"6ub7vi0t42tk\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679607-145564-hi-fructose-magazine-the-new-contemporary-art-magazinepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Hi-Fructose was founded by two artists by the name of Attaboy and Annie Owen in the year 2005. It is a magazine that is published quarterly. The art blog part is headed by Andy Smith. Hi-Fructose revolves around contemporary art and showcases the best artists of recent times. There is no fixed genre that it emphasizes. Each post highlights the works of a different artist, focusing on one notable work. A typical Hi-Fructose post also describes how the artist came up with the idea and the process behind the creation of the work. The post contains information about the artist and his/her quotes. Hi-Fructose appreciates and celebrates original artwork and inspires new artists to come up with better works. The blog is full of talented contributors and readers can expect as many as four posts every day!</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.artnews.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ARTnews Magazine&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679621-673801-artnews-com-the-leading-source-for-art-news-art-event-coveragepng.png\" data-image=\"zo9z4s6jzq9w\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679621-673801-artnews-com-the-leading-source-for-art-news-art-event-coveragepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Artnews is the oldest art magazine in the world. It would come as no surprise then that the content is rich and varied. Artnews has an art blog as well which publishes posts about art events, trends, artist profiles, art in general, as well as trending issues. With more than 703,000 followers on Instagram and 227,000 likes on Facebook, Artnews is also one of the most popular art blogs around. The blog has a separate section for reviews as well that contains hard-hitting journalism, a high-quality critique of artworks, and insightful reports. The &lsquo;retrospective&rsquo; section looks back at artworks from the past and treats readers with valuable opinions and meaningful research. The blog has a wide reader base that includes both amateurs as well as experts. With as many as 8 posts every day, ARTnews is a rich database of articles and resources related to art.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.artforum.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Artforum</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679635-45144-artforum-internationalpng.png\" data-image=\"9c9pj4naus8v\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679635-45144-artforum-internationalpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Artforum is a New York-based art blog. It revolves around contemporary art and publishes enlightening critiques of visual art exhibitions. It also publishes news and articles on trending topics and issues. The blog has a separate section for&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.artandeducation.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Art and Education</a>&nbsp;which has resources for aspiring artists who want to follow a career in their passion. Artforum has columns, shows, and a print media section as well. The blog also showcases works of present-day artists and provides valuable reviews. A part of the blog is completely dedicated to this. All in all, this blog brings together all art-related things in one place. You can even purchase merchandise and other artworks via this platform. It is a rather happening place for art enthusiasts with a minimum of 7 posts every day. The blog has 600,000 followers on Instagram and Twitter.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.contemporaryartdaily.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Contemporary Art Daily&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679650-898020-contemporary-art-daily-png.png\" data-image=\"kvtrm4lj9ze7\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679650-898020-contemporary-art-daily-png.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">As the name suggests, this blog publishes content that talks about contemporary art. Started in the month of November in 2008, readers can expect a minimum of 3 posts from them every day. The blog has content that covers contemporary art events and exhibitions organized on a global level. Contemporary Art Daily also showcases submissions by amateur artists. The blog contains archives, information about art exhibitions, reviews, trending matters, and much more. Art enthusiasts can sign up to receive weekly emails from the blog. A&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.pixpa.com/blog/how-to-write-blog-post\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">typical blog post</a>&nbsp;about an artwork displayed in an exhibition contains the name and bio of the artist, the artwork itself, the venue, date, and the organizers of the exhibition. The post sometimes contains a slideshow of all the works of the art exhibition.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.frankie.com.au/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Frankie Magazine</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574741390-876010-frankiejpg.png\" data-image=\"vqg7jh2t3zzr\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574741390-876010-frankiejpg.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\" /><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">This art publication from Australia is one of the most popular art blogs in the country. Content on the Frankie blog covers a wide range of domains. Art, craft, photography, design, music, film, and books are surprisingly just a few of them. You can find articles on cuisine, vintage artworks, and fashion as well. The Frankie blog also has a podcast section where you can enjoy the latest content published by them. Since Frankie Magazine is sort of like a Jack of all trades, its versatility is one of the major attractions for readers and art enthusiasts. The publication started in 2011 and comes up with a new post every week. You can also shop for products like diaries, calendars, books, and of course, printed issues of the Frankie magazine.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://moussemagazine.it/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Mousse&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679687-140082-mousse-magazinepng.png\" data-image=\"240qzk97qq85\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679687-140082-mousse-magazinepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Another art publication that dedicates its content to mostly contemporary artworks, Mousse originated in Milan, Italy in the year 2006. It is published twice a month in English and Italian. Mousse is a classy magazine that publishes interviews with some of the most reputed artists and curators from around the globe. Along with that, Mousse contains essays and critical analysis of contemporary artworks by esteemed critics and artists. It is printed in a pleasant tabloid format. The online blog also contains a rich variety of articles and distinctive editorials. You can also subscribe to emails from Mousse to keep yourself updated about the ongoings in the art world. Mousse is one of the best art blogs and magazines in our opinion. The publication radiates class and finesse.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.cassart.co.uk/blog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cass Art / Art Supplies Blog&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679722-516142-cass-artpng.png\" data-image=\"vfzvjs7ps9sz\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679722-516142-cass-artpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Cass Art is one of the best art blogs in the United Kingdom. Originating from London, Cass Art aims to inspire and propel new artists to the forefront. In general, Cass Art is an art supplies blog that ensures that talented and creative artists get the best prices on the highest quality of art materials in the market. The blog started in the year 2012 and since then has gathered more than 50,000 followers on Twitter and Facebook. The official website has categorized art supplies into painting, drawing, surfaces, craft, etc. It also has a separate section for products that are meant for kids. Not only this, Cass Art posts information about upcoming events in the world of art. Lastly, the blog also has information about art workshops in most of the important cities of England like Manchester, London, Liverpool, and Birmingham.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://blog.lostartpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Lost Art Press</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679743-25840-lost-art-presspng.png\" data-image=\"4bl6ud6qz9ay\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679743-25840-lost-art-presspng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">The Lost Art Press was founded in 2007 by two woodworkers, Jeff Hoffmann and Christopher Schwarz. The blog focuses on woodworking and publications related to it. You can find books, archives, and resources on the Lost Art Press. The aim of the blog is to create awareness about the &lsquo;lost art&rsquo; of woodworking. The blog encourages high-quality books, which are made with the finest of materials. The founding members share half of the profit with the authors and give them due credit. Apart from books, you can also buy tools like hammers, electrical saws, scrapers, and other similar articles. There is also a section for clothing and accessories. The blog has a small following on social media but don\'t let the numbers fool you. The blog is a hotspot for artists and woodworkers. Apart from the online blog, the Lost Art Press also sells books via small to medium-sized retailers.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.thisiscolossal.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Colossal</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679771-425069-colossal-art-design-and-visual-culture-png.png\" data-image=\"mllpqozderyn\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679771-425069-colossal-art-design-and-visual-culture-png.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">If the previous entry on the list wasn&rsquo;t impactful enough, Colossal stands true to its name and is one of&nbsp; the biggest art blogs in the United States. Launched in 2010 in Illinois, the blog publishes content about visual arts. Colossal covers a wide range of topics with the likes of photography, animation, design, painting, and drawing bossing the show. You can also find stuff related to installation art as well as street art. The blog is a vibrant collection of resources related to art, design, and visual culture. Colossal has a whopping fan following of more than a million followers on social media. The range of content is so diverse that it is fascinating. Head on to the blog and click on the &lsquo;More&rsquo; section to see a variety of categories and topics that you can explore. Lastly, you can buy funky merchandise in the e-commerce section of Colossal.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://spoke-art.com/blogs/news\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Spoke Art&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679788-742731-spoke-art-blog-spoke-artpng.png\" data-image=\"j910wgexx5ic\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679788-742731-spoke-art-blog-spoke-artpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Spoke Art is an Art gallery in San Francisco. It also publishes articles, reviews, and news. The blog celebrates pop art and contemporary art and publishes content related to them. Spoke Art also organizes art exhibitions and events. It also publishes artists&rsquo; profiles and editions. On the official website of the Spoke Art, you can check out merchandise like pins, books, clothes, collectibles, and toys. All in all, the Spoke Art space is a vibrant and happening place where art enthusiasts can enjoy original content by some of the most creative artists in the world. Articles and reviews by Spoke Art are insightful, resourceful, and valuable. Once you visit a page on the website which is dedicated to a particular genre of art, you can browse through the related events, featured exhibitions, and featured artists. You can purchase magazines and printed editions of Spoke Art as well.</span></p>', '2021-04-18', '');
INSERT INTO `tbl_blog` (`blog_id`, `blog_title`, `blog_subheader`, `blog_author`, `blog_image`, `blog_category`, `blog_published`, `blog_end_link`, `blog_yt_video`, `blog_body`, `blog_date`, `blog_tags`) VALUES
(71, 'Local Coming Soon', '', 'Malek Farag', '70c2ceefd07033070eac06aebe9a5e49.jpg', 1, 1, '', '', '<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">If you are a creative professional looking for some inspiration or love art and design and would like to&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.pixpa.com/blog/web-design-trends\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">keep up with current trends</a>, there are lots of art blogs that might help spark an idea and inspire you.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">We have put together a list of our favorite art blogs that you must follow in the coming year to jumpstart your creativity. This list covers art blogs written by artists, art critics, art lovers, or simply people who appreciate art and like to share their views.</span></p>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574743033-389837-art-blogsjpg.png\" data-image=\"rfxl93y7ms78\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574743033-389837-art-blogsjpg.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 2em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Here is our curated list of the Top 25 Art Blogs and Online Magazines</span></h2>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://hifructose.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Hi-Fructose</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679607-145564-hi-fructose-magazine-the-new-contemporary-art-magazinepng.png\" data-image=\"6ub7vi0t42tk\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679607-145564-hi-fructose-magazine-the-new-contemporary-art-magazinepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Hi-Fructose was founded by two artists by the name of Attaboy and Annie Owen in the year 2005. It is a magazine that is published quarterly. The art blog part is headed by Andy Smith. Hi-Fructose revolves around contemporary art and showcases the best artists of recent times. There is no fixed genre that it emphasizes. Each post highlights the works of a different artist, focusing on one notable work. A typical Hi-Fructose post also describes how the artist came up with the idea and the process behind the creation of the work. The post contains information about the artist and his/her quotes. Hi-Fructose appreciates and celebrates original artwork and inspires new artists to come up with better works. The blog is full of talented contributors and readers can expect as many as four posts every day!</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.artnews.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ARTnews Magazine&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679621-673801-artnews-com-the-leading-source-for-art-news-art-event-coveragepng.png\" data-image=\"zo9z4s6jzq9w\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679621-673801-artnews-com-the-leading-source-for-art-news-art-event-coveragepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Artnews is the oldest art magazine in the world. It would come as no surprise then that the content is rich and varied. Artnews has an art blog as well which publishes posts about art events, trends, artist profiles, art in general, as well as trending issues. With more than 703,000 followers on Instagram and 227,000 likes on Facebook, Artnews is also one of the most popular art blogs around. The blog has a separate section for reviews as well that contains hard-hitting journalism, a high-quality critique of artworks, and insightful reports. The &lsquo;retrospective&rsquo; section looks back at artworks from the past and treats readers with valuable opinions and meaningful research. The blog has a wide reader base that includes both amateurs as well as experts. With as many as 8 posts every day, ARTnews is a rich database of articles and resources related to art.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.artforum.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Artforum</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679635-45144-artforum-internationalpng.png\" data-image=\"9c9pj4naus8v\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679635-45144-artforum-internationalpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Artforum is a New York-based art blog. It revolves around contemporary art and publishes enlightening critiques of visual art exhibitions. It also publishes news and articles on trending topics and issues. The blog has a separate section for&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.artandeducation.net/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Art and Education</a>&nbsp;which has resources for aspiring artists who want to follow a career in their passion. Artforum has columns, shows, and a print media section as well. The blog also showcases works of present-day artists and provides valuable reviews. A part of the blog is completely dedicated to this. All in all, this blog brings together all art-related things in one place. You can even purchase merchandise and other artworks via this platform. It is a rather happening place for art enthusiasts with a minimum of 7 posts every day. The blog has 600,000 followers on Instagram and Twitter.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.contemporaryartdaily.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Contemporary Art Daily&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679650-898020-contemporary-art-daily-png.png\" data-image=\"kvtrm4lj9ze7\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679650-898020-contemporary-art-daily-png.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">As the name suggests, this blog publishes content that talks about contemporary art. Started in the month of November in 2008, readers can expect a minimum of 3 posts from them every day. The blog has content that covers contemporary art events and exhibitions organized on a global level. Contemporary Art Daily also showcases submissions by amateur artists. The blog contains archives, information about art exhibitions, reviews, trending matters, and much more. Art enthusiasts can sign up to receive weekly emails from the blog. A&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.pixpa.com/blog/how-to-write-blog-post\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">typical blog post</a>&nbsp;about an artwork displayed in an exhibition contains the name and bio of the artist, the artwork itself, the venue, date, and the organizers of the exhibition. The post sometimes contains a slideshow of all the works of the art exhibition.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://www.frankie.com.au/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Frankie Magazine</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574741390-876010-frankiejpg.png\" data-image=\"vqg7jh2t3zzr\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574741390-876010-frankiejpg.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\" /><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">This art publication from Australia is one of the most popular art blogs in the country. Content on the Frankie blog covers a wide range of domains. Art, craft, photography, design, music, film, and books are surprisingly just a few of them. You can find articles on cuisine, vintage artworks, and fashion as well. The Frankie blog also has a podcast section where you can enjoy the latest content published by them. Since Frankie Magazine is sort of like a Jack of all trades, its versatility is one of the major attractions for readers and art enthusiasts. The publication started in 2011 and comes up with a new post every week. You can also shop for products like diaries, calendars, books, and of course, printed issues of the Frankie magazine.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"http://moussemagazine.it/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Mousse&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679687-140082-mousse-magazinepng.png\" data-image=\"240qzk97qq85\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679687-140082-mousse-magazinepng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Another art publication that dedicates its content to mostly contemporary artworks, Mousse originated in Milan, Italy in the year 2006. It is published twice a month in English and Italian. Mousse is a classy magazine that publishes interviews with some of the most reputed artists and curators from around the globe. Along with that, Mousse contains essays and critical analysis of contemporary artworks by esteemed critics and artists. It is printed in a pleasant tabloid format. The online blog also contains a rich variety of articles and distinctive editorials. You can also subscribe to emails from Mousse to keep yourself updated about the ongoings in the art world. Mousse is one of the best art blogs and magazines in our opinion. The publication radiates class and finesse.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.cassart.co.uk/blog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cass Art / Art Supplies Blog&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679722-516142-cass-artpng.png\" data-image=\"vfzvjs7ps9sz\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679722-516142-cass-artpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Cass Art is one of the best art blogs in the United Kingdom. Originating from London, Cass Art aims to inspire and propel new artists to the forefront. In general, Cass Art is an art supplies blog that ensures that talented and creative artists get the best prices on the highest quality of art materials in the market. The blog started in the year 2012 and since then has gathered more than 50,000 followers on Twitter and Facebook. The official website has categorized art supplies into painting, drawing, surfaces, craft, etc. It also has a separate section for products that are meant for kids. Not only this, Cass Art posts information about upcoming events in the world of art. Lastly, the blog also has information about art workshops in most of the important cities of England like Manchester, London, Liverpool, and Birmingham.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://blog.lostartpress.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Lost Art Press</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679743-25840-lost-art-presspng.png\" data-image=\"4bl6ud6qz9ay\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679743-25840-lost-art-presspng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">The Lost Art Press was founded in 2007 by two woodworkers, Jeff Hoffmann and Christopher Schwarz. The blog focuses on woodworking and publications related to it. You can find books, archives, and resources on the Lost Art Press. The aim of the blog is to create awareness about the &lsquo;lost art&rsquo; of woodworking. The blog encourages high-quality books, which are made with the finest of materials. The founding members share half of the profit with the authors and give them due credit. Apart from books, you can also buy tools like hammers, electrical saws, scrapers, and other similar articles. There is also a section for clothing and accessories. The blog has a small following on social media but don\'t let the numbers fool you. The blog is a hotspot for artists and woodworkers. Apart from the online blog, the Lost Art Press also sells books via small to medium-sized retailers.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://www.thisiscolossal.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Colossal</a>&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679771-425069-colossal-art-design-and-visual-culture-png.png\" data-image=\"mllpqozderyn\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679771-425069-colossal-art-design-and-visual-culture-png.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">If the previous entry on the list wasn&rsquo;t impactful enough, Colossal stands true to its name and is one of&nbsp; the biggest art blogs in the United States. Launched in 2010 in Illinois, the blog publishes content about visual arts. Colossal covers a wide range of topics with the likes of photography, animation, design, painting, and drawing bossing the show. You can also find stuff related to installation art as well as street art. The blog is a vibrant collection of resources related to art, design, and visual culture. Colossal has a whopping fan following of more than a million followers on social media. The range of content is so diverse that it is fascinating. Head on to the blog and click on the &lsquo;More&rsquo; section to see a variety of categories and topics that you can explore. Lastly, you can buy funky merchandise in the e-commerce section of Colossal.</span></p>\r\n<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 1.5em 0px 0.75em; padding: 0px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: 500; color: #272727; font-size: 1.6em; line-height: 1.6em; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #000000;\" href=\"https://spoke-art.com/blogs/news\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Spoke Art&nbsp;</a></span></h3>\r\n<figure style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; color: #5b5b5b; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\"><img class=\" lazyloaded\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; max-width: 100%; opacity: 1;\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679788-742731-spoke-art-blog-spoke-artpng.png\" data-image=\"j910wgexx5ic\" data-src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/pixpa.com/com/articles/1574679788-742731-spoke-art-blog-spoke-artpng.png\" /></span></figure>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px 0px 1.26316em; padding: 0px; font-size: 1.13em; line-height: 1.8em; color: #242424; font-family: Lora, serif; background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; font-family: Lora;\">Spoke Art is an Art gallery in San Francisco. It also publishes articles, reviews, and news. The blog celebrates pop art and contemporary art and publishes content related to them. Spoke Art also organizes art exhibitions and events. It also publishes artists&rsquo; profiles and editions. On the official website of the Spoke Art, you can check out merchandise like pins, books, clothes, collectibles, and toys. All in all, the Spoke Art space is a vibrant and happening place where art enthusiasts can enjoy original content by some of the most creative artists in the world. Articles and reviews by Spoke Art are insightful, resourceful, and valuable. Once you visit a page on the website which is dedicated to a particular genre of art, you can browse through the related events, featured exhibitions, and featured artists. You can purchase magazines and printed editions of Spoke Art as well.</span></p>', '2021-04-18', '');

